history.content:
182 has 189 as a prereq, so that might not be a good idea. According to stat major friends, 154 is a terrible class. 

189 is a class that is simply hard or completely brutal depending on the professor. I haven't heard much about IEOR 142.

Also keep in mind that 189 fulfills a CS upper div, but the others do not.

I'm planning on doubling in DS and CS, but not sure which course to take to fulfill the Modeling, Learning... requirement and Human Ethics requirement:

Any suggestions/opinions on any of them would be really appreciated!

Modeling, Learning, Decision Making requirement:

- CS 182

- CS 189

- IND ENG 142

- STAT 154

Human Context and Ethics requirement:

- AMERSTD/AFRICAM C134

- HIST C184D / STS C104

- INFO 188

- ISF 100J

- PHILOS 121
